ion, natural language processing, or sensor fusion, ensuring that \nsubsequent layers receive clean and actionable inputs. \n  \n   \nRepresentation Layer: \nThe perception layer feeds into the representation layer, which transforms the raw \ninput into structured formats that are more manageable and efficient for the system \nto process. This layer uses models to represent the world, entities, and potential"), Document(metadata={'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 86}, page_content='data\nData \ncollection \nsystems are \noperational \n24/7 \nAt least 12 \nmonths of \nhistorical \ndata is \navailable \nInitial: Basic infrastructure, limited expertise, and early framework development. \nEmerging: Building core capabilities and developing talent, with early AI \nprojects in progress. \nDeveloping: Systematic integration of AI, skilled talent pool, and centralized \nAI governance. \nAdvanced: Full integration, mature AI capabilities, strong governance \nframeworks, and industry-leading innovation potential. \nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\n46\n \n \nD. Recommended Strategies \nVery High           High          Moderate           Initial \nReadiness \nLevel \nLevel 1: \nInitial \nLevel 2: \nEmerging \nLevel 3: \nDeveloping \nLevel 4: \nAdvanced \nCharacteristics\nMinimal \nunderstanding \nof AI \nExperimental AI \ninitiatives \nSystematic AI \nintegration \nTransformative \nAI capabilities \nKey \nIndicators \nLimited data \ninfrastructure \nBasic data \nintegration, \nisolated projects \nCentralized AI \ngovernance'), Document(metadata={'source': 'data\\raw_documents\\Ebook-Agentic-AI.pdf', 'chunk_id': 76}, page_content='Establishing Rigorous Benchmarks: Defining precise, quantifiable performance \nmetrics is essential for assessing the capabilities of agentic AI systems. These \nmetrics act as benchmarks to gauge AI effectiveness, identifying areas in need of \nimprovement. This, in turn, allows for the continuous refinement of AI systems t